					<dataqual>
						<lineage>
							<procstep>
								<procdesc>The New Jersey rail data is derived from MapInfo files from the New Jersey Port Authority with a source scale of 1:100,000.  Data were projected and converted to shapefiles.</procdesc>
								<procdate>2007</procdate>
								<srcused>MapInfo files from the New Jersey Port Authority</srcused>
							</procstep>
							<procstep>
								<procdesc>Separated passenger lines from freight/inactive lines.  Separate shapefiles created for NJT Rail, NJT Hudson-Bergen Light Rail, NJT Newark Subway, NJT Riverline, Amtrak, PATCO, and SEPTA lines.</procdesc>
								<procdate>May - September 2007</procdate>
							</procstep>
							<procstep>
								<procdesc>Features were redrawn based on the NJ Transit files, using onscreen digitizing with NJ DoT Roads (2005), River LINE PDF map (2004),  and NJ DEP Orthophotos (2002) as references.  Stations were snapped to line endpoints.  Attributes were added.</procdesc>
								<procdate>August 2007</procdate>
								<srcused>NJ DoT Roads</srcused>
								<srcused>NJ DEP Orthophotos</srcused>
								<srcused>River LINE PDF map</srcused>
							</procstep>
